data.description: Having gone missing seven years ago, the previously blind Prairie returns home, now in her twenties with her sight restored. While many believe she is a miracle, others worry that she could be dangerous.

data.title: Desperate Housewives
data.description: A close-knit group of housewives reside in Wisteria Lane. It may appear to be a seemingly perfect neighborhood but it hides many secrets, crimes, forbidden romances and domestic struggles.

data.title: Better Call Saul
data.description: The trials and tribulations of criminal lawyer Jimmy McGill in the years leading up to his fateful run-in with Walter White and Jesse Pinkman.

data.title: Bates Motel
data.description: An intimate look into the unraveling of Norman Bates' psyche throughout his teenage years.

data.title: The Punisher
data.description: After his revenge on those who murdered his family, aimless Marine veteran Frank Castle finds a new meaning in life as a vigilante known as "The Punisher".

data.title: Atypical
data.description: Sam, an 18-year-old on the autism spectrum, decides it's time to find a girlfriend, which sets Sam's mom on her own life-changing path as her son seeks more independence.

data.title: Dynasty
data.description: Follows two of America's wealthiest families as they feud for control over their fortune and their children.

data.title: This Is Us
data.description: A heartwarming and emotional story about a unique set of triplets, their struggles, and their wonderful parents.

data.title: The Good Place
data.description: Eleanor Shellstrop, a deceased saleswoman who lived a morally corrupt life, finds herself in a heaven-like afterlife in a case of mistaken identity and tries to hide her past in order to stay there.

data.title: Iron Fist
data.description: A young man is bestowed with incredible martial arts skills and a mystical force known as the Iron Fist.

data.title: The Rain
data.description: After a brutal virus wipes out most of the population, two young siblings embark on a perilous search for safety.

data.title: Mindhunter
data.description: In the late 1970s, two FBI agents broaden the realm of criminal science by investigating the psychology behind murder and end up getting too close to real-life monsters.

data.title: Revenge
data.description: An emotionally troubled young woman sets out to exact revenge against the people who wronged her father.

data.title: Luke Cage
data.description: When a sabotaged experiment gives him super strength and unbreakable skin, Luke Cage becomes a fugitive attempting to rebuild his life in Harlem and must confront his past and fight a battle for the heart of his city.

data.title: Scandal
data.description: A former White House Communications Director starts her own crisis management firm only to realize her clients are not the only ones with secrets.

data.title: The Defenders
data.description: Set a few months after the events of the second season of Daredevil, and a month after the events of Iron Fist, the vigilantes Daredevil, Jessica Jones, Luke Cage, and Iron Fist team up in New York City to fight a common enemy: Th...

data.title: Big Little Lies
data.description: The apparently-perfect lives of upper-class mothers of students at a prestigious elementary school unravel to the point of murder when a single mother moves to their quaint California beach town.

data.title: Insatiable
data.description: A disgraced, dissatisfied civil lawyer-turned-beauty pageant coach takes on a vengeful, bullied teenager as his client and has no idea what he's about to unleash upon the world.

data.title: The Mentalist
data.description: Famous "psychic", Patrick Jane, outs himself as a fake, and using his heightened observational skills and impeccable knowledge of the human psyche, he works with the police so he can find "Red John", the madman who killed his family.

data.title: The Crown
data.description: Follows the political rivalries and romances of Queen Elizabeth II's reign and the events that shaped Britain for the second half of the 20th century.

data.title: Chernobyl
data.description: In April 1986, the city of Chernobyl in the Soviet Union suffers one of the worst nuclear disasters in the history of mankind. Consequently, many heroes put their lives on the line in the following days, weeks and months.

data.title: iZombie
data.description: A medical resident finds that being a zombie has its perks, which she uses to assist the police.

data.title: Reign
data.description: Mary, Queen of Scots, faces political and sexual intrigue in the treacherous world of the French court.

data.title: A Series of Unfortunate Events
data.description: After the loss of their parents in a mysterious fire, the three Baudelaire children face trials and tribulations attempting to uncover dark family secrets.

data.title: Criminal Minds
data.description: The FBI's Behavioral Analysis Unit in Quantico helps police solve violent serial crimes using profiling. Team members analyze evidence and psychology to catch unknown subjects, but their demanding work affects personal lives.

data.title: Scream
data.description: A serialized anthology series that follows a group of teenagers being targeted by a masked serial killer.

data.title: The Haunting of Hill House
data.description: Flashing between past and present, a fractured family confronts haunting memories of their old home and the terrifying events that drove them from it.
